<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,152,567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,425,451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[327,496,425,450]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,496,425,450]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Bhatia serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[504,594,425,451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Metcalf" authorityName="Metcalf" box="[725,998,425,451]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guamensis">
<emphasis box="[725,881,425,450]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. guamensis</emphasis>
(Metcalf)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1069,1141,425,451]" name="Guam" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Guam</collectingCountry>
in head shape and shares the lateral serrated aedeagus with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kwon &amp; Lee" authorityName="Kwon &amp; Lee" box="[547,834,464,490]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koreana">
<emphasis box="[547,674,464,489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. koreana</emphasis>
Kwon &amp; Lee
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[905,976,464,490]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Korea</collectingCountry>
but differs from both species in having an elongate preatrium and the ventral processes oppressed to each other. The new species shares the structure of style with 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura" box="[305,637,541,567]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satsumensis">
<emphasis box="[305,477,542,567]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. satsumensis</emphasis>
(Matsumura)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[709,776,541,567]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Japan</collectingCountry>
but lacks the subapical processes to the shaft.
</paragraph>
